metadata.name: Visa to the stars #500
metadata.description:
Generative space scenes with an illustrative look.

Use the capture functions to export in big after opening it in its own window, the artwork is full of details.

Press SPACE to show/hide the menu

Control the camera and explore the scene with :
- Mouse Left : Rotate
- Mouse Right : Pan
- Mouse Middle : Zoom

I wrote an article about the project, with a technical breakdown of the piece at https://ulucode.com/wp/visa-to-the-stars/


Decent GPU REQUIRED, you can tune the performances with the "Quality" setting in the menu.
Better performances with Chrome.

Keyboard shortcuts:
SPACE : show/hide menu
A : toggle anti-aliasing
C : take a capture of the ccurrently selected resolution
R : reset camera position/orientation
S : display stats
P : pause animation

metadata.name: Zometric #244
metadata.description:
A journey into geometric shapes.
Real art is not hidden behind complicated and obscure forms. In this collection, we have tried to achieve a unique visual clarity by using the basic visual elements. A pure mixture between piet mondrian and paul klee. A combination of visual language of classical and modern art movements. Over 15 000 combination can be generated.
Made in p5.js

metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #433
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash — they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Electric Fangs #114
metadata.description:
The living, breathing human body is a vessel for desires; the brain artificially reshaped by the flickering light of Electric Fangs.

Electric Fangs is about our insatiable thirst for digital attention, like blood-craving vampires.

metadata.name: Bougainvillea #6
Brutalist #153
metadata.description:
from the depth
the architect ponder
reshape my world
in hollow order

#11
experimental vintage series

press "C" to turn on/off outlines
press "V" to turn on/off background objects and grid, if any present
press "B" to turn on/off rotation
press "N" to reload with different layout, 3 iterations to cycle through

press "UP arrow" to increase render scale multiplier by x1 (maximum is x4, default is x3)
press "DOWN arrow" to decrease render scale multiplier by x1 (minimum is x1)

press "S" to save png in live view

metadata.name: Bipole #110
metadata.description:
Two meandering paths are created with opposite flow vectors. The paths are drawn with a twisty drip brush.

Created for #tezos4tezos in May 2022.

Features 
- The amount each stroke's bristles twist as the path is drawn
- If each paths starts off strong or soft
- Splats at the starts and ends of the path
- Dark mode
- Monochrome or colored lines (colors from the p5riso palette)
- Paper fibers in the background
- 10% chance of dark orange and black lines

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 2400px by 1483px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.
